def: Tainter with, or constituting, barratry.-- Bar"ra*trous*ly, adv. Kent.
A period during which an obligor has a legal right to delaymeeting an obligation, esp. such a period granted, as to a bank, by amoratory law.
A petiole dilated into the form of a blade, and usually withvertical edges, as in the Australian acacias.
To hasten; to go in haste; -- also often with the reciprocalpronoun. [Rare, except in poetry] "My husband hies him home." Shak.The youth, returning to his mistress, hies. Dryden.
A teaching and impressing by frequent repetitions. Bp. Hall.
Of or pertaining to strangury. Cheyne.
An appearance as of a halo of light, surround the edges of darkobject
A weight of one hundred pounds avoirdupois; -- called in manyparts of the United States a Hundredweight.
